      "raw_text": "At this time, when irrigated prop\nerty is at the heighth OF its boom,\nalmost, suit started by Frank\nl.. Norton against the Interstate Ir-\nrigation Co. is particularly inter\nesting. Norton invested $3.50 in\nirrigated land in Kootenai county.\nIdaho, Oct. Is. 1906, He planted\nsugar beets to beat the band But\nthe beets didn't amount to much\nand he considers he has been\nbeat\" himself. So he wants the\nmost of his money back.\n\n\nHe alleges that he made repeat\ned demands on the company for\nwater for irrigation but they were\nUNDECIDED."
